        <name>10.2.3.5 Modulus and argument</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If \( \displaystyle{z_1 = {@z1@}}\) and&amp;nbsp;\( \displaystyle{z_2 = {@z2@}}\) find:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt; \( |z_1 z_2| = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&amp;nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt; \( \text{Arg}(z_1 z_2) = \)&amp;nbsp;[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]&amp;nbsp;[[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Give your answers to \(3\) d.p.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
  
  &lt;p&gt;\( z_1 = {@z1@} \) so \( |z_1| = {@r1@} \) and&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;\( \text{arg}(z_1) = {@theta1@}\)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\( z_2 = {@z2@} \) so \( |z_2| = {@r2@} \) and&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;\( \text{arg}(z_2) = {@theta2@}\)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt; \( |z_1 z_2| = |z_1||z_2| = {@ta1@} \)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;\( \text{arg}(z_1 z_2) = \text{arg}(z_1) + \text{arg}(z_2) = {@ta2@} \)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have in mind that \( -\pi &amp;lt; \text{arg}(z) \leq \pi \) so you may need to add or subtract a \( \pi\) from your \( \text{arg} \) results.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
